bug.short_desc: Fedora Media Writer lists two different entries for an usb stick
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1203020 USB stick is listed multiple times
Description of problem: Fedora Media Writer lists two different entries for an usb stick.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): mediawriter-3.96.0-0.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible: Always reproducible, after triggering bug 1377604. Not reproducible otherwise.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. I hit bug 1377604 (https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1377604). 2. Back to the main menu, I selected the LXDE spin. 3. I clicked on "Create Live USB". 4. I clicked on the combobox in order to select the correct device.
Actual results: Two entries appear in the combobox, even if there is only one stick connected.
Expected results: Only one entry should appear in the combobox.
Additional info: This is the output of "lsusb" (the stick is 002/005): Bus 001 Device 002: ID 8087:8001 Intel Corp. Bus 001 Device 001: ID 1d6b:0002 Linux Foundation 2.0 root hub Bus 003 Device 001: ID 1d6b:0003 Linux Foundation 3.0 root hub Bus 002 Device 004: ID 05e3:0723 Genesys Logic, Inc. GL827L SD/MMC/MS Flash Card Reader Bus 002 Device 003: ID 05e3:0608 Genesys Logic, Inc. Hub Bus 002 Device 002: ID 046d:c52b Logitech, Inc. Unifying Receiver Bus 002 Device 005: ID 058f:6387 Alcor Micro Corp. Flash Drive Bus 002 Device 001: ID 1d6b:0002 Linux Foundation 2.0 root hub
The triggering bug is fixed so this should be fixed too. Please let us know after the package update (most likely incoming tomorrow)
